str2: To conform to. From sun and a derivative of schema; to fashion alike, i.e. Conform to the same pattern.
This; he, she, it.
From the same as aei; properly, an age; by extension, perpetuity; by implication, the world; specially a Messianic period.
But, except, however. Neuter plural of allos; properly, other things, i.e. contrariwise.

str2: To transform, transfigure. From meta and morphoo; to transform.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Renewing; a renewal or change of heart and life. From anakainoo; renovation.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Probably from the base of ginosko; the intellect, i.e. Mind; by implication, meaning.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
From dokimos; to test; by implication, to approve.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Neuter Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.

A primary word; 'good'.
Acceptable, well-pleasing (especially to God), grateful. From eu and arestos; fully agreeable.
And, even, also, namely.
From telos; complete; neuter completeness.
An act of will, will; plur: wishes, desires. From the prolonged form of ethelo; a determination, i.e. choice or inclination.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
